{"root":{"data":{"text":"Hypothesis: Ligase Functions as E3 Ligase"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"Protein Expression & Purification"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"A. Express and purify the suspected E3 ligase in a cell line (e.g., HEK293T)."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"B. Test activity in an in vitro ubiquitination assay using E1 (activating enzyme), E2 (conjugating enzyme), ubiquitin, and suspected E3 ligase.","layout":null},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"BioE3 Setup (Specific Substrate Identification)"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"A. Design BirA-E3 fusion constructs (suspected E3 ligase fused to BirA biotin ligase)."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"B. Generate worms expressing BirA-E3 fusions under controlled induction (e.g., with doxycycline)."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"C. Introduce bioUbL (biotin-labeled ubiquitin or SUMO) into worms to facilitate proximity-dependent labeling."},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"BioE3 Experiment (In Vivo)"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"A. Biotin Labeling: Induce expression of the BirA-E3 fusion and incubate worms with biotin to allow proximity-dependent biotinylation of substrates."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"B. Pull-down: Capture biotinylated proteins using streptavidin beads for enrichment."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"C. Identification of substrates by LC-MS (mass spectrometry) to determine the specific targets of the E3 ligase."},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"Validation of Identified Substrates"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"A. Western Blot Validation: Confirm the ubiquitination of top hits using immunoblotting (e.g., with ubiquitin or specific substrate antibodies)."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"B. Orthogonal Validation Methods: Validate substrate ubiquitylation using complementary approaches such as His-ubiquitin pulldown assays."},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"Functional Assays on Substrates"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"A. Knockdown or knockout of the identified substrate using RNA interference (RNAi) or CRISPR."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"B. Assess the functional consequences (e.g., degradation, localization changes, or cellular phenotype)."},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"Substrate Specificity Confirmation"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"A. Mutagenesis of E3 Ligase: Generate catalytically inactive mutants of the E3 ligase (e.g., by mutating the RING domain or catalytic cysteine)."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"B. Compare substrate binding and ubiquitination between wild-type and mutant ligase to confirm substrate specificity."},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"Exploration of Ligase Pathways and Conditions"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"A. Study the impact of external stimuli (e.g., chemical treatments, growth factors) on E3 ligase activity and substrate recognition."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"B. Explore the broader cellular pathways in which the ligase is involved using network analysis and gene ontology."},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"Conclusion"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"A. Confirm E3 ligase activity by demonstrating direct ubiquitination of specific substrates."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"B. Identify the ligaseâ€™s role in regulating cellular pathways through targeted ubiquitination events."},"children":[]}]}]},"template":"default","theme":"fresh-blue","version":"1.4.43"}